{
  "title": "Benchmarking Edge Run times Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide demonstrates how to measure the performance of an edge application built with FastAPI and Python 3.12+ using benchmarking libraries like aiohttp_benchmark.",
  "key_points": [
    "Install required packages: FastAPI, Uvicorn, aiohttp, and aiohttp_benchmark.",
    "Create a simple FastAPI application with an endpoint to test.",
    "Use aiohttp_benchmark to send multiple requests to the FastAPI endpoint and measure the response times.",
    "Analyze the obtained results to compare the performance of different scenarios or optimizations."
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n# Import necessary libraries\nimport asyncio\nimport aiohttp\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, Request\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\n@app.get('/')\nasync def root(request: Request):\n    return {'message': 'Hello World'} \n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n# Benchmark the FastAPI endpoint\nasync def benchmark():\n    async with aiohttp.ClientSession() as session:\n        tasks = []\n        for _ in range(100):\n            tasks.append(session.request('GET', 'http://localhost:8000/'))\n        responses = await asyncio.gather(*tasks)\n        return [response.content for response in responses]\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    asyncio.run(benchmark()) \n```"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required to run the examples.",
    "FastAPI version 0.72.0 or later is needed for the given code.",
    "Uvicorn and aiohttp versions may vary depending on your project needs."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Make sure to adjust the number of requests in the benchmark function according to your hardware capabilities.",
    "Consider using multiple processes or threads for testing if you have access to a multi-core machine.",
    "The provided examples are simplified and serve as a starting point. Real-world applications may require more complex setups."
  ]
}
